=North America=
In large cities across North America, hawkers are commonly known as street vendors, who sell snack items, such as deep-fried bananas, cotton candy, fried noodles, beverages like bubble tea, and ice cream, along with non-edible  items, such as jewelry, clothes, books, and paintings. Hawkers are also found selling various items to fans at a sports venue; more commonly, this person is simply referred to as a stadium vendor.<ref>[http://www.joesportsfan.com/?p=147 The Stadium Vendor Hierarchy] webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100118132421/http://www.joesportsfan.com/?p=147 |date=January 18, 2010 </ref><ref>cite web|url=http://www.mentalfloss.com/blogs/archives/25302 |title=Nine Famous Baseball Stadium Vendors |publisher=Mentalfloss.com |date=2009-05-06 |accessdate=2013-08-18</ref>

